# CapeControl Email Configuration
# Add these environment variables to enable live email sending

# SMTP Server Configuration (Example for Gmail)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password

# Email Settings
FROM_EMAIL=noreply@capecontrol.com
ADMIN_EMAIL=zeonita@gmail.com

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env in the project root
# 2. Update SMTP_USERNAME and SMTP_PASSWORD with your actual credentials
# 3. For Gmail, use an App Password instead of your regular password
# 4. Restart the application to load the new configuration
#
# Gmail App Password Setup:
# 1. Enable 2-factor authentication on your Google account
# 2. Go to Google Account Settings > Security > App passwords
# 3. Generate a new app password for "Mail"
# 4. Use that password in SMTP_PASSWORD
#
# Other Email Providers:
# - Outlook: smtp-mail.outlook.com:587
# - Yahoo: smtp.mail.yahoo.com:587  
# - Custom SMTP: Use your provider's settings
